The paper deals with the development of a Brain Computer Interface (BCI) using electroencephalographic (EEG) signals and classification algorithms. This falls under the broad category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves signal processing and computer vision techniques, which are covered by cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper deals with human-computer interaction, which is covered by cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks and optimization techniques, which are covered by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
